1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available.]

2
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:55,520
[Crossroad Bistro]

3
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:36,280
Have you picked a wedding date?

4
00:02:36,880 --> 00:02:38,720
Should be on the 20th of next month.

5
00:02:40,040 --> 00:02:41,560
Have you told your parents?

6
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:44,040
No.

7
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:46,400
Forgive me for saying this,

8
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:48,960
but I still think you need to tell them about it.

9
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:56,520
We've not spoken for two years.

10
00:02:57,640 --> 00:02:59,800
My dad has burnt all the bridges

11
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,640
to separate me and Peng Pai.

12
00:03:01,640 --> 00:03:03,440
He said he never wants to see me again.

13
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:07,320
What about your mom?

14
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,600
You're not talking to her, either?

15
00:03:08,880 --> 00:03:10,080
She's on my dad's side.

16
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:12,800
I am almost thirty.

17
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:15,160
Don't I even have the right to choose

18
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:16,320
who to spend my life with?

19
00:03:17,920 --> 00:03:21,079
When it comes to this, parents usually mean well.

20
00:03:21,920 --> 00:03:23,560
Maybe they just handled it poorly.

21
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:26,920
Does that mean I have to do as they say?

22
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:29,640
First of all, I am not a homewrecker.

23
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:31,600
Second, I don't ask them for money.

24
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:32,840
What have I done wrong?

25
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,800
People can change the way of handling things.

26
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,160
But it's them who handled it wrong should change.

27
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:38,040
Take it easy.

28
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:39,640
It's like someone stepped you on your feet.

29
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:41,680
Don't try to persuade me.

30
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:43,800
I will find a time to tell them

31
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:45,960
after I'm done with the wedding.

32
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:48,720
Well...

33
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:49,960
What other family members are coming?

34
00:03:50,760 --> 00:03:51,720
My sister.

35
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:53,800
She's applying for a visa now.

36
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:57,280
She's the only one I hope to see in the family.

37
00:03:58,360 --> 00:04:00,760
Do you like this wedding dress?

38
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:01,600
Yes.

39
00:04:24,720 --> 00:04:26,360
Rinse.

40
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:31,000
Monitor the patient's vital signs.

41
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,240
The endoscope is standing by.

42
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:46,360
Defibrillator charged.

43
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:47,760
Clear.

44
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:49,120
Discharge.

45
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:51,800
Prepare for another one.

46
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:52,720
Clear.

47
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:54,159
Discharge.

48
00:04:56,320 --> 00:04:57,480
It's not working.

49
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:59,560
Again!

50
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:00,640
Clear.

51
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:01,440
Discharge.

52
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:18,760
Hey, man.

53
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:21,000
Welcome back.

54
00:05:27,440 --> 00:05:29,120
Peng Pai!

55
00:05:30,520 --> 00:05:31,600
How is he?

56
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:33,800
He's fine now.

57
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,920
He went into a shock

58
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:38,920
because of the rupture of his brain tumor.

59
00:05:41,960 --> 00:05:43,560
We've made a surgical incision

60
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:45,000
and removed the tumor.

61
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,320
But during the surgery,

62
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:47,840
he suffered a sudden cardiac arrest.

63
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:50,120
We almost lost him.

64
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:53,080
Don't be so sad.

65
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:54,800
He's safe now, right?

66
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:58,080
Everything will be alright.

67
00:06:42,080 --> 00:06:42,920
Slow down.

68
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:44,200
Don't fall.

69
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:45,560
Ma'am.

70
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:48,120
You're back.

71
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,280
Sir.

72
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:05,680
Hello?

73
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:07,040
Sis.

74
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:08,120
You up?

75
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:10,360
I wasn't sleeping.

76
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:12,560
Embrace yourself.

77
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:15,400
I want to tell you some exciting news.

78
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:16,160
What?

79
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:20,280
I got my visa!

80
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:25,520
Do you know how hard it was for me,

81
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:27,160
a single woman

82
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:28,360
with no fixed assets

83
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:29,760
or a stable job, to get it?

84
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:31,120
They must worry that I'd tear my passport apart

85
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:32,960
after I got off the plane and never come back.

86
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:36,080
You should see the look of the visa officer today.

87
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:38,400
He kept rolling his eyes at me.

88
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:39,840
Bao Xue.

89
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,400
I need to tell you something.

90
00:07:59,960 --> 00:08:00,840
You can't

91
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:02,320
tell anyone.

92
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:03,280
Okay?

93
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:04,680
Don't worry.

94
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:05,880
I won't tell anyone.

95
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:07,600
The doctor

96
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:09,360
said he is already out of danger, right?

97
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:12,200
So, don't put too much pressure on yourself.

98
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:14,840
The most important thing right now

99
00:08:14,840 --> 00:08:15,800
is to take care of him.

100
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:17,680
Anything else can wait till he recovers.

101
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:19,880
Okay.

102
00:08:19,880 --> 00:08:21,320
I'm gonna hang up now.

103
00:08:21,640 --> 00:08:22,880
Get some sleep.

104
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:24,320
Bye-bye.

105
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:36,000
-Morning.
-Morning.

106
00:08:37,039 --> 00:08:38,440
Morning.

107
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:41,039
You went to take the meds for me the other day.

108
00:08:41,799 --> 00:08:43,200
I was having such a headache

109
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:44,360
so I closed my eyes.

110
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:47,160
Then suddenly, I felt

111
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:49,080
I was shrinking to this big

112
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:51,480
and thrown into

113
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:52,800
a bottomless pit.

114
00:08:53,040 --> 00:08:54,120
I just kept falling.

115
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:55,560
It was like a nightmare.

116
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,360
I wanted to open my eyes, but I couldn't.

117
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:58,200
I couldn't wake up.

118
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,320
I just kept falling.

119
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:01,360
Then what happened?

120
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:04,600
I couldn't remember anything after that.

121
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:05,680
I was already here when I woke up.

122
00:09:07,640 --> 00:09:09,200
You almost died.

123
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:11,360
The surgery took 5 hours.

124
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:18,440
Well, I'm here now.

125
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:21,320
Hi, you're awake!

126
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:22,920
Doc.

127
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:26,520
We think you can be discharged now.

128
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:28,480
You can go home and rest.

129
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:30,680
Everything is fine?

130
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:31,600
Yes.

131
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:33,400
So far, so good.

132
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:37,200
So, you can go back home

133
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:38,280
and take your time to recover.

134
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,240
Thank you, Doc.

135
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:43,720
You should thank your wife.

136
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:45,720
She was here the whole time and praying for you.

137
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:47,480
Thank you.

138
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:05,760
I sent the design of the invitation to your email.

139
00:10:19,760 --> 00:10:23,080
[A separation agreement]

140
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:28,400
Xiaoyu.

141
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:30,920
Where is the blue scarf

142
00:10:30,920 --> 00:10:32,920
you bought me?

143
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:42,160
What is it?

144
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:44,480
Why are you upset?

145
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:45,360
Not feeling well?

146
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,040
What's wrong?

147
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:53,360
What's with the tantrum?

148
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:55,160
You think I'm throwing a tantrum?

149
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:57,760
Tell me what's on your mind.

150
00:10:58,040 --> 00:10:59,400
It's filled with curse words.

151
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:06,800
Xiaoyu.

152
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,720
Didn't we agree

153
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:12,120
when we first got together

154
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:14,040
that we will tell each other everything

155
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:15,320
that's on our minds

156
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:17,200
so that we don't have to guess?

157
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,400
It will

158
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:20,080
make us

159
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:21,240
trust each other more.

160
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:22,400
Trust?

161
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:23,840
You don't deserve to use that word.

162
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:25,400
Why not?

163
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:31,600
Read the email your lawyer sent you first.

164
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:52,480
Why are you quiet now?

165
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:53,680
Thinking of how you can

166
00:11:53,680 --> 00:11:55,000
lie to me, right?

167
00:11:57,680 --> 00:11:58,640
Can you let me explain?

168
00:11:58,640 --> 00:11:59,840
About what?

169
00:12:00,680 --> 00:12:02,120
Do you wanna say

170
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:03,720
that you lied to me because you love me?

171
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:04,640
I didn't lie to you.

172
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:05,280
What?

173
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:06,440
I didn't lie.

174
00:12:07,280 --> 00:12:08,520
You didn't?

175
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:11,800
You said your divorce was finalized five years ago.

176
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:13,160
But you're still married to her.

177
00:12:13,160 --> 00:12:15,280
If I didn't want to marry you so badly,

178
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:16,080
you wouldn't have even

179
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:17,480
sent the divorce paper to your ex, right?

180
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:18,760
We've separated for 7 years.

181
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:19,840
7 years!

182
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:21,360
I have no feelings for her.

183
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:22,880
We just didn't sign the divorce paper.

184
00:12:24,080 --> 00:12:25,040
I get it now.

185
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:27,320
I am less important than a divorce paper.

186
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:29,080
You're twisting my words.

187
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:30,480
Excuse me?

188
00:12:31,040 --> 00:12:32,960
I should be grateful that you got ill.

189
00:12:33,520 --> 00:12:35,400
Otherwise, I'll never know about all this.

190
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:37,120
As long as you're still married,

191
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:38,480
I'll be the homewrecker.

192
00:12:39,480 --> 00:12:40,960
Your wife and your daughter will think

193
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:42,080
you want to divide your property

194
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:44,040
because you've got a calculating lover abroad.

195
00:12:44,040 --> 00:12:45,280
Thank you very much.

196
00:12:45,280 --> 00:12:46,200
Because of you,

197
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:49,200
I've now become the kind of person I hate the most.

198
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:52,240
I've never intended to lie to you.

199
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:53,480
I've always wanted to get a divorce,

200
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:55,200
but I've been too busy to deal with it.

201
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:56,240
I couldn't go back to China

202
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:57,840
and sign the divorce paper.

203
00:12:58,360 --> 00:12:59,760
That's the only reason why I didn't do it!

204
00:13:09,480 --> 00:13:10,400
Xiaoyu.

205
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:12,200
I'll just divorce her

206
00:13:12,520 --> 00:13:14,680
and give her and my daughter my property in China.

207
00:13:14,680 --> 00:13:16,080
Then we can live

208
00:13:16,080 --> 00:13:18,400
a happy life here, okay?

209
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:20,080
What about your will?

210
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:24,080
It's written clearly on the will

211
00:13:24,920 --> 00:13:27,160
that if you die of any cause,

212
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:28,920
90% of your property

213
00:13:28,920 --> 00:13:31,360
will go to your daughter.

214
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:33,000
The other 10% will go to your wife.

215
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:34,280
Did I remember it right?

216
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:35,960
It was outdated.

217
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:39,160
I can update it after I divorce her.

218
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:49,040
I've spent five of my best years with you.

219
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:52,160
When you were sick, I was running around

220
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:53,720
taking care of you.

221
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,840
What am I to you?

222
00:13:56,560 --> 00:13:57,600
A nurse?

223
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:00,480
Even a nurse gets paid daily.

224
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:01,280
And me?

225
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:03,800
I'm your secret lover.

226
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:05,160
What are you talking about?

227
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:14,800
Calm down, will you?

228
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:19,320
It all happened so quickly.

229
00:14:19,320 --> 00:14:21,200
I didn't prepare for it.

230
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:22,880
Nevertheless,

231
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:24,600
it was never my intention to do this to you.

232
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:26,080
You know that, right?

233
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:27,480
I know it a bit too well.

234
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:30,240
It's all written on the document.

235
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:31,960
I'm not illiterate.

236
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:33,000
I can read.

237
00:14:33,920 --> 00:14:35,160
You're despicable.

238
00:14:36,760 --> 00:14:37,760
Think all you want.

239
00:14:38,040 --> 00:14:38,880
Whatever.

240
00:14:42,480 --> 00:14:43,960
I made a mistake about the divorce.

241
00:14:44,280 --> 00:14:45,280
I wanted to deal with it later.

242
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:46,360
It's just a matter of time.

243
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:47,400
My ex-wife was fine with it.

244
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:48,400
Stop right there.

245
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:50,720
You haven't divorced her yet.

246
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:51,760
She's still your wife.

247
00:14:51,760 --> 00:14:52,800
Not your ex-wife.

248
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:54,320
Do you have to get all technical about it?

249
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:55,480
Shouldn't I?

250
00:14:55,480 --> 00:14:57,280
No!

251
00:14:57,280 --> 00:14:59,200
I almost married you.

252
00:15:12,840 --> 00:15:14,440
I think we can

253
00:15:14,920 --> 00:15:16,400
take a break and calm down.

254
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:18,040
I'll leave for Manchester for a 3-day business trip.

255
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:19,720
We can talk it over

256
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:21,760
when I come back.

257
00:15:22,360 --> 00:15:23,440
I will keep

258
00:15:24,320 --> 00:15:25,040
my promise to you.

259
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:42,480
Xiaoyu, I am back

260
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:48,880
Xiaoyu?

261
00:16:04,520 --> 00:16:05,400
Xiaoyu?

262
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:41,440
Sorry, the subscriber you dialed is out of service.

263
00:16:54,160 --> 00:16:55,240
Hello, sis.

264
00:16:55,640 --> 00:16:56,880
It's midnight where you are, right?

265
00:16:56,880 --> 00:16:58,440
Have you not slept yet or already gotten up?

266
00:17:00,160 --> 00:17:01,360
How's everything going?

267
00:17:01,360 --> 00:17:03,160
Which date should I book my flight for?

268
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:06,319
That I don't care.

269
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:08,520
I booked my flight for yesterday.

270
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:10,040
What?

271
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:11,560
Where were you going?

272
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:14,359
I'm in Beijing visiting my grandma and my sister.

273
00:17:40,820 --> 00:17:44,300
[Ep01]

274
00:19:42,640 --> 00:19:43,880
Xiaoyu?

275
00:19:52,160 --> 00:19:53,360
Grandma.

276
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:58,080
Why are you back?

277
00:20:01,840 --> 00:20:02,600
Grandma.

278
00:20:04,040 --> 00:20:04,960
Great.

279
00:20:07,960 --> 00:20:09,680
Just spend some time with me.

280
00:20:09,680 --> 00:20:11,040
Don't buy anything.

281
00:20:11,040 --> 00:20:12,360
Just a token of my gratitude.

282
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:13,600
Yeah, granny.

283
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:15,640
It's time that she did it.

284
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:16,920
These are all premium snacks.

285
00:20:16,920 --> 00:20:18,800
I'll take them all if you don't like them.

286
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:20,160
You wish.

287
00:20:20,160 --> 00:20:21,080
I like them.

288
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:22,640
Right.

289
00:20:22,640 --> 00:20:24,360
Grandma, keep them all.

290
00:20:24,360 --> 00:20:25,800
These are yours.

291
00:20:25,800 --> 00:20:28,080
There's no such thing as enough Bestore snacks.

292
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:29,680
Granny.

293
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:30,360
When I was little,

294
00:20:30,360 --> 00:20:31,880
you used to peel walnuts for us.

295
00:20:31,880 --> 00:20:33,640
Today, I'll peel walnuts for you.

296
00:20:34,320 --> 00:20:35,720
Great, thanks.

297
00:20:37,520 --> 00:20:39,040
Thank you, grandma.

298
00:20:39,040 --> 00:20:41,400
You're using my sweet gesture to please her?

299
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:43,080
How could you do that?

300
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:43,880
Xiaoyu.

301
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:47,320
You've never had a full-time job

302
00:20:47,320 --> 00:20:49,480
since you finished your postgraduate study.

303
00:20:52,040 --> 00:20:55,160
There's no such thing as a full-time job anymore.

304
00:20:55,160 --> 00:20:56,200
They're all temps.

305
00:20:57,760 --> 00:21:00,240
Even government officers are contract employees.

306
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:01,600
They can quit whenever they want to.

307
00:21:02,480 --> 00:21:03,720
Life is slow abroad,

308
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:05,040
so I've become lazy and casual

309
00:21:05,040 --> 00:21:06,800
after staying there for long.

310
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:08,040
You can't be like this.

311
00:21:08,280 --> 00:21:09,600
You're young.

312
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:11,800
You can't just sit around all the time

313
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:12,920
like us old people.

314
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:14,240
Yeah.

315
00:21:14,920 --> 00:21:15,760
I think

316
00:21:16,440 --> 00:21:18,160
I won't go back for now.

317
00:21:18,160 --> 00:21:20,280
I'll live here with you for a while.

318
00:21:20,280 --> 00:21:22,440
I'll move out once I find

319
00:21:22,440 --> 00:21:23,880
a good job and an apartment.

320
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:24,920
What do you say?

321
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:27,520
No problem.

322
00:21:27,760 --> 00:21:30,080
But I'll be upfront with you.

323
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:31,560
Don't stay for too long.

324
00:21:31,560 --> 00:21:33,040
I'm used to living here alone.

325
00:21:33,040 --> 00:21:34,200
It's kinda inconvenient

326
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:35,680
with someone else here.

327
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:38,120
Okay.

328
00:21:41,040 --> 00:21:42,160
Granny.

329
00:21:42,520 --> 00:21:44,840
I also love your sweet-and-sour ribs.

330
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:46,080
I've mentioned it several times

331
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:48,120
and you didn't even make them once.

332
00:21:49,520 --> 00:21:51,080
It's been years since she last had this dish.

333
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:53,680
Just now,

334
00:21:54,160 --> 00:21:55,880
when I glanced over Xiaoyu,

335
00:21:56,320 --> 00:21:58,040
I almost didn't recognize you.

336
00:21:58,040 --> 00:22:00,480
She is getting prettier and prettier.

337
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:01,440
You, on the contrary,

338
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:03,000
are getting uglier.

339
00:22:04,160 --> 00:22:07,000
Granny! I am what they call a "second-glance beauty."

340
00:22:08,320 --> 00:22:10,400
That's why you are not famous yet.

341
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:12,800
The directors always choose beauty at first glance.

342
00:22:13,840 --> 00:22:15,360
You are one of those first-glance beauties.

343
00:22:15,360 --> 00:22:16,800
But you don't even have a proper career.

344
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:18,000
What's a proper career?

345
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:18,840
Like yours?

346
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:20,360
Of course.

347
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:21,320
I don't steal or rob people.

348
00:22:21,320 --> 00:22:22,760
I love my country.

349
00:22:22,760 --> 00:22:24,840
It's better than someone
 who hasn't found her career path.

350
00:22:26,040 --> 00:22:27,920
When you can't find the right path,

351
00:22:28,120 --> 00:22:30,360
it's better to just stop where you are.

352
00:22:30,360 --> 00:22:31,160
I...

353
00:22:31,960 --> 00:22:33,320
You haven't changed a bit.

354
00:22:34,200 --> 00:22:36,200
Two minutes into a nice conversation

355
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:37,920
and you're already arguing.

356
00:22:38,080 --> 00:22:38,880
Dinner is ready.

357
00:22:39,680 --> 00:22:41,560
She's been picking on me since I was a kid.

358
00:22:41,560 --> 00:22:44,200
I can take whatever criticism comes my way.

359
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:45,600
I picked on you 'cause you were a loser.

360
00:22:46,280 --> 00:22:47,520
When we were at school,

361
00:22:47,520 --> 00:22:49,400
you didn't even know
 how to simplify a complex fraction.

362
00:22:50,480 --> 00:22:53,160
Just look at those roles you play.

363
00:22:53,160 --> 00:22:55,280
You can't even get a medium close-up.

364
00:22:55,520 --> 00:22:58,360
I have to hit pause to find you in a scene.

365
00:22:58,720 --> 00:22:59,960
You're 25 already.

366
00:22:59,960 --> 00:23:01,520
Yet you are still one of the extras.

367
00:23:02,240 --> 00:23:03,760
What are you thinking?

368
00:23:04,680 --> 00:23:05,840
Once

369
00:23:05,840 --> 00:23:07,120
I have a goal in life,

370
00:23:07,120 --> 00:23:08,560
I have the courage

371
00:23:08,560 --> 00:23:10,320
and an inexhaustible passion to achieve it.

372
00:23:10,520 --> 00:23:12,360
You're four years older than me.

373
00:23:12,360 --> 00:23:14,160
Let's talk about what you've achieved in life.

374
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:16,280
Yes, Xiaoyu.

375
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:20,840
I opened a coffee shop.

376
00:23:20,840 --> 00:23:23,160
But then it went out of business.

377
00:23:24,520 --> 00:23:25,680
How come?

378
00:23:27,360 --> 00:23:28,680
Business

379
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:30,360
is complicated.

380
00:23:31,640 --> 00:23:32,600
Come on.

381
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:33,880
Stop with those

382
00:23:33,880 --> 00:23:35,760
empty excuses, alright?

383
00:23:36,040 --> 00:23:38,000
Running a business is hard work.

384
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:38,760
But you're always sleeping.

385
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:40,560
How can you work day and night on business?

386
00:23:40,560 --> 00:23:41,280
Yeah.

387
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:42,680
I can't get up early.

388
00:23:42,680 --> 00:23:43,480
I can't stay up late.

389
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:44,880
Sis.

390
00:23:44,880 --> 00:23:45,760
I admire you.

391
00:23:45,760 --> 00:23:46,400
I really do.

392
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:48,800
You've always kept the virtue

393
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:50,720
of being lazy.

394
00:23:51,520 --> 00:23:53,440
You just have to slap me right in the face, right?

395
00:23:53,440 --> 00:23:55,400
No way! Your face is too pretty.

396
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,640
I don't have the heart to slap you.

397
00:23:56,640 --> 00:23:57,240
Let me kiss you.

398
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:58,120
Come on.

399
00:23:58,120 --> 00:23:59,720
Stop it.

400
00:23:59,720 --> 00:24:00,720
Just eat.

401
00:24:01,040 --> 00:24:03,360
You were like this when you were kids,

402
00:24:04,200 --> 00:24:05,480
always arguing when you were together.

403
00:24:06,480 --> 00:24:07,360
The big sister

404
00:24:07,840 --> 00:24:08,840
had to be the best in every aspect.

405
00:24:09,240 --> 00:24:10,080
The little one

406
00:24:10,080 --> 00:24:11,320
always messed around.

407
00:24:11,720 --> 00:24:14,760
Xiaoyu couldn't win an argument with Bao Xue

408
00:24:14,760 --> 00:24:17,040
so she'd use fists instead of words.

409
00:24:17,400 --> 00:24:21,640
Then Bao Xue would jump around like a monkey.

410
00:24:21,840 --> 00:24:23,440
But she's someone

411
00:24:23,440 --> 00:24:25,920
who never learns.

412
00:24:26,160 --> 00:24:27,720
She'd follow you around

413
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:28,880
calling you sis

414
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:30,280
when you were

415
00:24:30,280 --> 00:24:31,560
still mad.

416
00:24:32,640 --> 00:24:33,720
When did that ever happen?

417
00:24:33,720 --> 00:24:35,280
I don't remember it.

418
00:24:35,280 --> 00:24:36,880
Stop it.

419
00:24:37,160 --> 00:24:39,400
Your brain is like a giant sieve.

420
00:24:40,120 --> 00:24:40,640
Yeah.

421
00:24:40,640 --> 00:24:42,440
I only remember the useful things.

422
00:25:24,920 --> 00:25:26,080
You Shanshan?

423
00:25:26,960 --> 00:25:28,360
Are you You Shanshan?

424
00:25:30,080 --> 00:25:31,000
You are...

425
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:32,560
I was on the flight to Lhasa on 14th May.

426
00:25:34,240 --> 00:25:35,720
It's you!

427
00:25:35,720 --> 00:25:36,600
That girl...

428
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:37,920
Which girl?

429
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:39,360
Yeah, I'm Si Meng.

430
00:25:39,360 --> 00:25:40,960
What a coincidence! You live in the neighborhood?

431
00:25:40,960 --> 00:25:43,080
No, I just shop here often.

432
00:25:43,080 --> 00:25:44,400
I've been meaning to thank you.

433
00:25:44,400 --> 00:25:46,040
If you hadn't consoled me and talked to me,

434
00:25:46,040 --> 00:25:47,400
I would've been falling apart.

435
00:25:47,400 --> 00:25:48,920
Don't mention it.

436
00:25:48,920 --> 00:25:50,240
We're of similar age,

437
00:25:50,240 --> 00:25:51,560
but clearly, you haven't gone through

438
00:25:51,560 --> 00:25:52,600
as much as I did.

439
00:25:52,600 --> 00:25:54,640
You gave me a chance to be the big sister.

440
00:25:55,320 --> 00:25:56,920
You can go before me.

441
00:25:56,920 --> 00:25:59,240
I can't do that. There are so many people behind you.

442
00:25:59,240 --> 00:26:00,360
I'll use my card.

443
00:26:13,320 --> 00:26:15,640
I thought we'd agreed to it.

444
00:26:17,360 --> 00:26:20,280
Just give me 10% more of the share, okay?

445
00:26:22,400 --> 00:26:23,560
Whose purse is it?

446
00:26:23,560 --> 00:26:25,080
Who left a purse here?

447
00:26:27,560 --> 00:26:29,400
Let me see. It seems to be my friend's purse.

448
00:26:31,360 --> 00:26:32,520
I'll take it. Thanks.

449
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:34,120
You Shanshan.

450
00:26:36,080 --> 00:26:36,400
You Shanshan!

451
00:26:36,400 --> 00:26:37,240
I'll give you

452
00:26:37,240 --> 00:26:38,880
more share in the next project.

453
00:26:39,520 --> 00:26:40,200
You Shanshan.

454
00:26:41,480 --> 00:26:42,440
You Shanshan!

455
00:28:20,280 --> 00:28:21,600
I've refilled your glass for you.

456
00:28:21,600 --> 00:28:22,160
Okay.

457
00:28:41,880 --> 00:28:44,000
Drive me back to the firm first.

458
00:28:44,240 --> 00:28:44,800
Okay.

459
00:28:45,600 --> 00:28:46,360
You Shanshan!

460
00:28:49,880 --> 00:28:50,920
What are you doing here?

461
00:28:51,520 --> 00:28:52,640
Did you lose something?

462
00:28:52,880 --> 00:28:54,000
Is this yours?

463
00:28:55,800 --> 00:28:57,400
You were so careless.

464
00:28:57,760 --> 00:28:59,840
I didn't even realize that I lost my purse.

465
00:29:00,080 --> 00:29:01,520
Check if everything is in there.

466
00:29:01,520 --> 00:29:02,240
There's no need.

467
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:04,160
You wouldn't bring it to me if anything is missing.

468
00:29:06,560 --> 00:29:07,400
Thanks.

469
00:29:08,160 --> 00:29:09,240
You helped me last time.

470
00:29:09,240 --> 00:29:10,440
I helped you today.

471
00:29:10,440 --> 00:29:12,480
I have repaid your favor.

472
00:29:13,080 --> 00:29:14,080
Are you free now?

473
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:15,080
Yes.

474
00:29:16,760 --> 00:29:18,360
You must be busier than me.

475
00:29:18,680 --> 00:29:20,080
That depends on how you see it.

476
00:29:20,560 --> 00:29:22,120
Sometimes, I've got my plate full all day.

477
00:29:22,120 --> 00:29:23,960
Sometimes, I don't have anything to do.

478
00:29:24,160 --> 00:29:25,480
You, on the contrary,

479
00:29:25,480 --> 00:29:26,560
need to do all the housework

480
00:29:26,560 --> 00:29:27,880
while raising two kids.

481
00:29:27,880 --> 00:29:29,320
You must be busy all the time.

482
00:29:30,080 --> 00:29:31,680
Thanks for understanding.

483
00:29:32,920 --> 00:29:35,760
I went to Lhasa to sponsor a charity event.

484
00:29:35,760 --> 00:29:36,880
Why did you go there?

485
00:29:37,320 --> 00:29:38,240
Don't get me started.

486
00:29:38,240 --> 00:29:40,440
My parents insisted on driving to Lhasa themselves.

487
00:29:40,960 --> 00:29:42,800
They're so cool!

488
00:29:42,800 --> 00:29:44,840
But my mom was hit by AMS the minute she got there

489
00:29:44,840 --> 00:29:46,120
and ended up in a hospital.

490
00:29:46,120 --> 00:29:47,600
I was worried sick.

491
00:29:47,600 --> 00:29:49,480
So I decided to book a ticket and fly there.

492
00:29:49,720 --> 00:29:52,080
Unfortunately, the tickets for that day were sold out.

493
00:29:52,080 --> 00:29:53,120
So, I booked the flight to Lhasa

494
00:29:53,120 --> 00:29:54,760
that transferred from Chengdu.

495
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:56,160
Are they alright?

496
00:29:56,160 --> 00:29:57,560
They are.

497
00:29:57,560 --> 00:29:58,880
But I almost died.

498
00:30:00,400 --> 00:30:01,840
Seriously, looking at you now,

499
00:30:01,840 --> 00:30:05,280
I can recall how scared you were the other day.

500
00:30:05,280 --> 00:30:06,040
I really can.

501
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:07,920
You cried so hard that your eyes were swollen.

502
00:30:07,920 --> 00:30:09,200
You wouldn't listen to me at all.

503
00:30:09,200 --> 00:30:11,360
I was like, "Stop crying, girl.

504
00:30:11,400 --> 00:30:13,080
Just leave it to fate."

505
00:30:13,440 --> 00:30:14,840
I didn't want to cry,

506
00:30:14,840 --> 00:30:16,040
but I was too scared.

507
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:17,960
My legs kept shaking the whole time, you know?

508
00:30:18,520 --> 00:30:19,720
I admire you.

509
00:30:20,040 --> 00:30:21,960
How did you manage to stay calm in danger?

510
00:30:22,200 --> 00:30:24,560
I've experienced all that life has to offer.

511
00:30:24,560 --> 00:30:26,040
It wouldn't be such a pity

512
00:30:26,040 --> 00:30:27,160
if I just dropped dead

513
00:30:27,160 --> 00:30:28,280
without having to suffer.

514
00:30:28,280 --> 00:30:29,560
In 18 years,

515
00:30:29,560 --> 00:30:30,840
I'd come back a new man in my next life.

516
00:30:31,160 --> 00:30:31,920
Right.

517
00:30:31,920 --> 00:30:33,360
That is exactly what you said to me.

518
00:30:33,840 --> 00:30:35,160
I felt much more relaxed

519
00:30:35,160 --> 00:30:36,560
after hearing those words.

520
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:39,480
It's lunchtime.

521
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:41,080
Let's have lunch together.

522
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:42,760
My washing machine has been acting up.

523
00:30:42,760 --> 00:30:43,960
I'm having it repaired this afternoon.

524
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:45,080
I need to go back and wait for the repairman.

525
00:30:46,480 --> 00:30:48,760
I thought you had something important!

526
00:30:49,360 --> 00:30:50,280
I know

527
00:30:50,760 --> 00:30:52,600
a repairperson for washing machines.

528
00:30:52,600 --> 00:30:53,800
He's an expert.

529
00:30:53,800 --> 00:30:55,640
He'll fix your washing machine for good.

530
00:30:55,640 --> 00:30:57,400
Who is he? Recommend him to me.

531
00:30:58,440 --> 00:31:01,480
Cancel your appointment

532
00:31:01,480 --> 00:31:02,280
and give me your address.

533
00:31:02,280 --> 00:31:03,640
I'll ask him to go there now.

534
00:31:03,960 --> 00:31:05,000
I'll go with you.

535
00:31:05,440 --> 00:31:06,600
You want to come with me?

536
00:31:06,920 --> 00:31:08,400
Don't you have to work?

537
00:31:10,880 --> 00:31:12,680
It's a bit awkward to say it out loud

538
00:31:13,520 --> 00:31:14,920
but I own the whole firm,

539
00:31:14,920 --> 00:31:16,720
so no one's checking my attendance.

540
00:31:18,600 --> 00:31:20,280
It's so good to be a boss.

541
00:31:21,080 --> 00:31:21,880
I'll cancel it then.

542
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:22,600
Yeah.

543
00:31:27,480 --> 00:31:28,520
Granny!

544
00:31:30,880 --> 00:31:33,040
What are you making? Smells so good!

545
00:31:33,040 --> 00:31:34,840
Red-braised pork, your favorite.

546
00:31:36,000 --> 00:31:37,040
Great.

547
00:31:37,560 --> 00:31:39,200
I'll cook the eggplant, then we're good to go.

548
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:40,240
Okay.

549
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:42,680
Granny, where is Xiaoyu?

550
00:31:43,720 --> 00:31:44,840
Still sleeping.

551
00:31:46,600 --> 00:31:48,000
Still?

552
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:49,080
She doesn't go to bed at night

553
00:31:49,080 --> 00:31:50,280
and doesn't get up in the morning.

554
00:31:50,560 --> 00:31:51,880
Every day at noon,

555
00:31:51,880 --> 00:31:53,600
she gets out of her bed

556
00:31:53,600 --> 00:31:55,000
after I put lunch on the table.

557
00:31:55,560 --> 00:31:56,240
After lunch,

558
00:31:56,240 --> 00:31:58,200
she just leaves the dirty dishes in the sink.

559
00:31:58,280 --> 00:31:59,760
Leave them.

560
00:31:59,880 --> 00:32:00,680
Just ignore them

561
00:32:00,680 --> 00:32:01,640
and wait for her to do the dishes.

562
00:32:01,840 --> 00:32:03,040
Then, I might have to wait

563
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:05,440
until the dishes are covered in mold.

564
00:32:05,440 --> 00:32:07,320
She's unbearable!

565
00:32:07,960 --> 00:32:09,040
Wait here.

566
00:32:09,040 --> 00:32:10,480
I'll get her out of bed.

567
00:32:23,320 --> 00:32:24,400
What?

568
00:32:25,080 --> 00:32:27,320
You're having sweet dreams

569
00:32:27,640 --> 00:32:29,520
while granny is doing all the work!

570
00:32:30,160 --> 00:32:31,800
Older people need less sleep.

571
00:32:32,400 --> 00:32:33,720
I'm still young.

572
00:32:34,120 --> 00:32:35,040
I need to sleep.

573
00:32:36,920 --> 00:32:39,000
Then, don't sleep before her eyes.

574
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:39,960
